steps.instruction:
- Finely chop shallot for 2 tablespoons
- Coarsely chop tomatoes
- Coarsely chop chorizo
- Preheat large saute pan on medium for 2 to 3 minutes
- Place oil in pan with shallots, capers and chorizo, cook for 3 to 4 minutes or until the shallots have softened, sit occasionally 
- Stir in tomatoes, italian seasoning and red pepper, cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until tomatoes are soft and saucy
- Reduce heat to medium low
- Nestle fish into the sauce
- Pour wine over fish
- Cover
- Cook for 5 to 6 minutes or until the fish registers 145F
- Chop oregano
- Spoon sauce over fish
- Sprinkle chopped oregano over top
